Pour the @water for the rice{300%ml} into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting lid.

Stir in the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @Onion{1}. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large frying pan{} on medium heat. Once hot, add the onion, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and fry, stirring occasionally, until golden, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, trim the @Baby Cucumber{1} and thinly slice into rounds. Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30%g}.

Trim the @Baby Gem Lettuce{1}, halve lengthways, then thinly slice.

== Dressing ==

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the @Red Wine Vinegar{12%ml}, two thirds of the @Sugar{1.5%tsp} and the @Olive Oil{1%tbsp}(for the dressing). Set aside.

== Onions ==

Once the onions are golden, add the remaining sugar and cook until caramelised, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Transfer to a #small bowl{} and cover to keep warm.

Wipe out the (now empty) #frying pan{} and return to medium-high heat (no oil).

== Beef and Bacon ==

Once hot, add the @British Beef Mince{240%g} and @British Smoked Bacon Lardons{90%g} and fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Use a spoon to break it up as it cooks. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the beef is browned, drain and discard any excess fat. Add the garlic and fry for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @Beef Stock Paste{10%g}, @Water for the Sauce{100%ml} and @Tomato Ketchup{2%tbsp} to the pan, then stir until combined.

Cook until the sauce has thickened, ~{2-4%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

== Assembly ==

Once everything's cooked, add the baby gem and cucumber to the bowl of dressing and toss to coat.

Fluff up the rice with a fork and divide between your bowls.

Spoon the beef and bacon over one side of the rice and add the salad to the other side. Top with the caramelised onions.

Sprinkle over the cheese and drizzle the @Burger Sauce{45%g} over the beef to finish.

Enjoy!